title: La Rochelle, no. 57 West Seventy-fifth Street, Northeast corner Columbus Avenue.

text:
46 West 75th Street, south side, west of Columbus Avenue.
About 1911.

West 75th Street, east from (about No. 36 on right) a point east of Columbus Ave., to Central Park West. At the latter point are the Kenilworth and the Hotel San Remo occupying the N.W. and S.W. corners respectively.

September 29, 1936.

W.P.A. Photo.
Federal Art Project.

West 75th Street, west from (No. 50 on left) a point east of Columbus Ave. (Sixth and Ninth Aves. Elevated Line thereon), to the North (Hudson) River. The five private dwellings on the left are Nos. 50 to 58. At the corner is a 6-story apartment house, No. 60 (also 313-315 Columbus Ave.). Opposite the latter is the 7-story Del Monte, 100-102 (also 306-316 Columbus Ave.) and another apartment house located at the S.W. corner of Columbus Ave.

September 29, 1936.

W.P.A. Photo.
Federal Art Project.
